## 2. Data Model — Place is the Atomic Unit

**Never expose raw Apify video records to the UI.** Every piece of data rendered must come from a resolved `Place` document.

```ts
// src/features/places/types.ts
interface Place {
  id_place: string           // Google Place ID (primary) or local UUID (fallback)
  name: string               // Canonical resolved name
  location: {
    address: string          // Human-readable: "El Tunco, La Libertad, El Salvador"
    lat: number
    lng: number
  }
  category: PlaceCategory    // 'beach' | 'restaurant' | 'nightlife' | 'other'
  videos: RawApifyVideo[]    // Evidence — never rendered directly
  trending: {
    likes: number
    views: number
    normalized: number       // 0–1 for reranking
  }
  sentiment: {
    score: number            // 0–1 composite
    summary: string          // LLM-generated human-readable summary (gets embedded)
  }
  description: string        // AI-generated summary of food, services, vibe
  embedding_text: string     // The string vectorised and stored in Upstash
  updatedAt: Date
}
```

---

## 3. Retrieval Flow — Retrieve → Rerank

The search pipeline is **always two stages**. Never return raw vector results to the UI without reranking.

```
user query (natural language)
  → embed with OpenAI (src/lib/openai)
  → Upstash vector search → top 30 candidates   (src/features/search/services)
  → rerank by composite score:
      0.5 × semantic_similarity
      0.3 × normalized_trending
      0.2 × sentiment_score
  → return top 10 to the UI
```

Sentiment weighting rule: negative comment sentiment acts as a **penalty**, not just a weak positive. A place the crowd trashes must be docked even if the creator hyped it.

---

## 4. Next.js 16 Paradigm (React Server Components)

- **Server Components by default.** Fetch place data and run vector queries directly in server components. Do not move fetching to the client.
- **Client Components (`"use client"`):** Required for the map (`features/map/`), search input interactions, and the AI chat box. Push the directive to the leaf level — wrap only the interactive part, not the whole page.
- **The explore page** (`app/explore/page.tsx`) renders the initial list server-side (SSR) for SEO. The map panel is a client island mounted alongside it.

---

## 5. Code & TypeScript Standards

- **Strict typing:** Every value must have an interface or type in `src/types/` or in its feature's `types.ts`. Never use `any`. The `Place` type is the source of truth — any field stored in Upstash metadata must be reflected here first.
- **Styles:** Tailwind CSS exclusively. Use `cn()` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional class concatenation.
- **Embedding text is immutable at query time.** Never mutate `embedding_text` after it has been vectorised without also re-running the OpenAI embedding and upserting the new vector to Upstash.

---

## 6. External Services — Client Responsibility

Each `src/lib/` module owns exactly one external dependency. No feature may import an SDK directly; it must go through `src/lib/`.

| Service | Module | Used by |
|---|---|---|
| MongoDB | `src/lib/mongodb/` | `features/users/services` (app: usuarios, sesiones, etc.) |
| Upstash Vector | `src/lib/upstash/` | `features/places/services`, `features/search/services`, `features/ingestion/services` |
| OpenAI Embeddings | `src/lib/openai/` | `features/ingestion/services`, `features/search/services` |
| Gemini | `src/lib/gemini/` | `features/ingestion/services` |
| Google Geocoding | `src/lib/geocoding/` | `features/ingestion/services` |

---

## 7. Ingestion Pipeline Rules

The pipeline lives entirely in `src/features/ingestion/services/`. It is a **batch script**, not a live API route.

1. `apify.ts` — fetches raw video records; outputs `RawApifyVideo[]`
2. `geocoding.ts` — resolves place name → `place_id` + `lat/lng` via `src/lib/geocoding`
3. `sentiment.ts` — calls Gemini on aggregated captions + comments; outputs `{ score, summary }`
4. `embeddings.ts` — builds `embedding_text`, calls OpenAI, upserts vector to Upstash using `place_id` as the vector ID

**Upsert rule:** always upsert by `place_id` in Upstash. Re-running is idempotent. Never insert a duplicate place — resolve/dedup via `findPlaceByIdPlace` / `findPlaceNearby` before upsert.

